        <updated>2022-01-14T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[In some of the assignments, you may be asked to update the badge link on the repository README file.]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In some of the assignments, you may be asked to update the badge link on the repository README file. </p><ul><li>Click on the <strong>Actions</strong> Tab at the top of your repository.<ul><li><img alt="image001" src="/assets/images/image001-c457e135f0879f3c1d777ad59a0cba09.png" width="937" height="299"></li></ul></li><li>Navigate to the <strong>Assignment Checks</strong> action job.<ul><li><img alt="image002" src="/assets/images/image002-a5f375a1de6a48d4c77a0b92d23d07fd.png" width="1920" height="491"></li></ul></li><li>Copy the badge.<ul><li><img alt="image003" src="/assets/images/image003-71fe039993eaa563c28bcf5f0e40192f.png" width="1271" height="589"></li></ul></li></ul><p>P.S.: In most assignments, I created a small script that automatically updates the link for you when you install the repository's dependencies using <code>npm install</code></p>]]></content>
