        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Visual Studio Code Settings and Extensions Sync]]></title>
        <id>vscode-extensions</id>
        <link href="https://it3049c.github.io/blog/vscode-extensions"/>
        <updated>2022-01-13T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[In my demo videos, you may notice that my Visual Studio Code IDE, provides with me with a lot of cheaters, helpers, and utilities that makes development a little easier.]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In my demo videos, you may notice that my Visual Studio Code IDE, provides with me with a lot of cheaters, helpers, and utilities that makes development a little easier.
In this post, I'm sharing some instructions for how you can setup you VSCode IDE with the same settings and extensions I have here.</p><p>To get started:</p><ol><li>you're going to need to install the Settings <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=Shan.code-settings-sync" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sync Extension</a> on VSCode.</li></ol><ul><li>Go to the link and click install. It will open VSCode and open the extension page</li><li>Click on <code>install</code> to download the extension<img alt="image 1" src="/assets/images/1-7869250a8e1f91fe347a8524eb46fd60.png" style="border:1px solid black;margin-bottom:2em"></li></ul><ol start="2"><li>Once installed open VSCode Command Palette using:</li></ol><ul><li>For Windows: <code>ctrl</code>+<code>shift</code>+<code>P</code></li><li>For Mac: <code>cmd</code>+<code>shift</code>+<code>P</code></li></ul><ol start="3"><li><p>In the command palette, type <code>Sync: Download Settings</code></p><img alt="image 2" src="/assets/images/2-a970a4edcf5b86f612c393c9b783ffea.png" style="border:1px solid black;margin-bottom:2em"></li><li><p>On the Following Screen, click on Download Public Gist and type in <code>416f36fd3c23571ecab1d3f3a5815fea</code></p><img alt="image 3" src="/assets/images/3-ec10a37e07fd8f2fb10fbcb4e0fafc29.png" style="border:1px solid black;margin-bottom:2em"></li><li><p>Open the command palette and type <code>Sync: Download Settings</code> again and watch the extensions get installed.</p></li><li><p>You may need to close VSCode and open it again for all extensions to take effect.</p></li></ol><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_mojV" id="some-of-my-extensions">Some of my Extensions<a class="hash-link" href="#some-of-my-extensions" title="Direct link to heading">​</a></h2><ul><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=formulahendry.auto-close-tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Auto Close Tag</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=formulahendry.auto-rename-tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Auto Rename Tag</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=mgmcdermott.vscode-language-babel" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Babel JavaScript</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=EditorConfig.EditorConfig" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">EditorConfig for VS Code</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ESLint</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=oderwat.indent-rainbow" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">indent-rainbow</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=christian-kohler.path-intellisense" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Path Intellisense</a></li><li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=GitHub.copilot" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Copilot</a></li></ul>]]></content>
